{"name":"Mathlib.Init.Data.Nat.Lemmas","instances":[{"typeNames":["Nat"],"name":"Nat.instLinearOrderNat","className":"LinearOrder"},{"typeNames":["Nat","Dvd.dvd","Nat.instDvdNat"],"name":"Nat.decidable_dvd","className":"Decidable"}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Init.Data.Nat.Basic","Mathlib.Init.Algebra.Functions"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Data/Nat/Lemmas.lean#L839-L839","name":"Nat.pow_eq","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Data/Nat/Lemmas.html#Nat.pow_eq","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Data/Nat/Lemmas.lean#L836-L837","name":"Nat.pow_succ'","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Data/Nat/Lemmas.html#Nat.pow_succ'","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Data/Nat/Lemmas.lean#L822-L834","name":"Nat.repr_length","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Data/Nat/Lemmas.html#Nat.repr_length","doc":"The core implementation of `Nat.repr` returns a String with length less than or equal to the\nnumber of digits in the decimal number (represented by `e`). For example, the decimal string\nrepresentation of any number less than 1000 (10 ^ 3) has a length less than or equal to 3. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Data/Nat/Lemmas.lean#L794-L820","name":"Nat.to_digits_core_length","docLink":"./Mathlib/Init/Data/Nat/Lemmas.html#Nat.to_digits_core_length","doc":"The String representation produced by toDigitsCore has the proper length relative to\nthe number of digits in `n < e` for some base `b`. Since this works with any base greater\nthan one, it can be used for binary, decimal, and hex. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Init/Data/Nat/Lemm